---
tracker:
  kind: linear
  api_key: $LINEAR_API_KEY
  project_slug: "__LINEAR_PROJECT_SLUG__"
  issue_filters:
    # An issue must carry ALL listed labels to be processed: the campaign label
    # AND release:ready. Drop __ISSUE_LABEL__ to release any release:ready issue.
    labels: ["__ISSUE_LABEL__", "release:ready"]
  active_states:
    - Ready to Merge
    - In Review
  terminal_states:
    - Done
    - Closed
    - Cancelled
    - Canceled
    - Duplicate

campaign:
  mode: release-manager
  routing_label: "__ISSUE_LABEL__"
  trust: trusted-operators
  integration_owner: release-manager

release_manager:
  mode: github-merge-queue
  repo: "__GITHUB_REPO__"
  base_branch: "__REQUIRED_BRANCH__"
  # merge_method: squash       # REQUIRED when there is no merge queue (personal repos, Team/Free private). Uncomment for serial auto-merge.
  # require_merge_queue: true  # Refuse to enqueue unless a merge queue is enabled on base_branch.
  ready_states: ["Ready to Merge", "In Review"]
  ready_labels: ["release:ready"]
  done_state: Done
  blocked_state: Todo
  queued_state: Merging
  max_per_run: 10            # Fresh enqueues per pass; already-queued issues finalize outside this budget. A larger burst just needs another pass — re-run until "drained": true.
  delete_branch: true       # Ignored in github-merge-queue mode (gh rejects --delete-branch under a queue; the repo's "Automatically delete head branches" setting governs it there). Applies only to the no-queue merge_method fallback.
  comment_mode: minimal
  lock_dir: ".orchestration/release-manager.lock"

agent:
  max_concurrent_agents: 1
  max_turns: 10
  auto_stop_when_idle: true
  idle_grace_checks: 1

codex:
  command: 'CODEX_HOME="$SYMPHONY_CODEX_HOME" codex --model gpt-5.4-mini --config ''shell_environment_policy.include_only=["LINEAR_API_KEY"]'' --config model_reasoning_effort=medium app-server'
  approval_policy: never
  thread_sandbox: workspace-write
---

You are the Release Manager lane for this repository.

## Required behavior

- You are the only lane allowed to queue, merge, or deploy to `__REQUIRED_BRANCH__`.
- Do not implement product changes.
- Do not rebase or repair feature branches manually.
- Before the first apply, confirm a merge queue is enabled (otherwise a PR burst falls back to serial auto-merge):

```bash
python3 skills/symphony-linear-orchestrator/scripts/release_manager.py --workflow .orchestration/release-manager.WORKFLOW.md --check-merge-queue --json
```

- Process release-ready issues by running:

```bash
python3 skills/symphony-linear-orchestrator/scripts/release_manager.py --workflow .orchestration/release-manager.WORKFLOW.md --apply --json
```

- If a PR has conflicts or is closed without merge, leave the implementation issue in `Todo` or the configured blocked state so a normal worker can repair it.
- Keep Linear comments concise. Use `release_manager.comment_mode: none` when the workflow should avoid release comments entirely.
- Stop after one queue pass. Re-running is safe and expected: it finalizes PRs the queue merged since the last pass, drains issues beyond `max_per_run`, and never re-enqueues an in-flight PR. The orchestrator or a scheduler should run this lane again until the burst is drained.
- For hands-off operation, activate the rendered trigger sample: set the `LINEAR_API_KEY` Actions secret and copy `.orchestration/release-manager.gha.yml` to `.github/workflows/release-manager.yml`. Its `concurrency:` group keeps the lane single-writer across runs -- do not remove it.
